story.title: Imaginary Friend
story.storyDescription: Maggie: Dani, are you still up??

messages.text: Can you come get me and Zoe and bring us to your house?
I can’t believe you went to babysit back at that house
I told her she needed to stop talking to him
After I did, the glass on the family portrait in the den shattered
Do you think she broke it?
She was standing nowhere near it!
The fire alarms also started going off in the house
I think that maybe this is all just a coincidence
Don’t tell me that! I told you about my dream last time!
You know I don’t totally believe in ghosts, Maggie
Something is here. I can feel it all the time
Omg, I can hear her talking to him in her room
I just found this outside her door:
The hairs on the back of my neck just stood up
I don’t know what to do.
Listen, maybe she just saw a horror movie or something
Stop trying to explain this away! I’m not crazy!
They’re in Bali. I couldn’t get them at the hotel
Do you think they know about this?
I don’t know, they left before I got there
Omg, I can hear her talking to him in her room
Again, not saying I believe in this stuff, but…there this website
Diedinhouse.com, you can check if something happened there
What’s the address, I’ll look it up
I don’t know that you want to know
The house used to belong to the Hurston family
In 1972,  a man murdered his wife and child, then was shot by police
Omg, Dani please come get me
I can’t stay here two more nights
Alex and I will drive over right now
I think in the meantime, maybe just go play with her
Just standing there staring at me
Ask her what she was doing in her room
She said playing a game with Robert
….and that Robert doesn’t like what I’m doing right now
Did you tell her FUCK ROBERT!?
Get me out of here now
She said they’re taking a trip to the basement to meet his wife and kid
I did, and she just stomped back into her room!
Go get her, bring her downstairs. We’ll be there in ten
THE DOOR JUST SLAMMED BEFORE I COULD GET OUT!!!
We’re calling 911 and we’re driving as fast as we can
She’s saying she’s going to play with Adele!
Do you think she’s already in the basement??
I don’t think you should go down there
I have to! I can’t leave her alone!
You guys will be here soon right??
We’ve got one more block and we’ll be with you
Omg. I just saw some man in the window, staring out at us
Her parents never left for their trip
And she’s here staring at me…
Grab her and bring her upstairs NOW
She says to call her Adele
The police just turned the corner! We’re coming in
